Despite only releasing this week, Red Dead Redemption 2 has already been rated as the best Xbox One and PlayStation 4 game ever. Metacritic has positioned the new Rockstar Games release atop it’s all-time rankings – with scores of 98/100 for the Xbox One version, and 97/100 on PlayStation 4. This positions the game above legendary titles including Grand Theft Auto V, Metal Gear Solid, and The Witcher 3. Meanwhile, IGN has awarded the game with a 10/10 rating, labeling it “one of the greatest games of the modern age.” Red Dead Redemption 2 follows in the wake of the original Red Dead Redemption game, which was released in 2010 to critical acclaim and a 95/100 Metacritic rating.